      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RUSSIAN REIGN (3) also returns after just one run in the maiden prep, an inglorious fifth of six over this trip at Hawkesbury 20 weeks ago. Was very green on that occasion so expect a bit more this time with the race experience on board. Can be a sharp improver and the most appealing one to side with. MONOCRU (4) is back after a five-month break. Hit the line well to finish a close second over this distance at Kembla at the only run when last in work. Recent trial winner who should be in for a strong campaign. STELLAA LASS (6) might need more ground now but the effort on debut over this distance was encouraging.",
